{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 14:20:30.919943", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"dns_server\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dns_port_blocked\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional, not part of submission):\n- On dns_server, remove or modify the nftables rules that drop tcp/udp dport 53 in the inet filter table (input/output/forward chains) so DNS traffic is accepted.\n- Verify with tcpdump and dig from a host that queries succeed and responses are seen.\n- Consider adding explicit accept rules for established/related traffic and for 53/udp/53/tcp before any generic drop rules, and then remove the specific drops.\n- Persist and test changes carefully; review why those drop rules were added (automation, hardening policy, or misconfiguration) and update deployment processes to prevent recurrence.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2188, "output_tokens": 173, "total_tokens": 2361, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
